40:32.889 --> 40:35.187
...would you consider that
a binding promise?

40:35.392 --> 40:36.858
- Absolutely.
- Yeah?

40:36.893 --> 40:39.589
Then again, there are always ways
around such things.

40:39.896 --> 40:41.659
- Like?
- For example...

40:41.898 --> 40:46.164
...if I promised a woman's father
I would not see her...

40:46.403 --> 40:50.271
...I would simply shut my eyes
while she serviced my manhood.

40:52.409 --> 40:54.502
That's actually a cool way to look at it.

40:54.537 --> 40:56.208
And a very gross way.

41:12.429 --> 41:15.364
He asked me not to go to the Hukilau.
I'm not going there.

41:15.932 --> 41:17.490
I'm not doing anything wrong.

41:24.441 --> 41:26.636
Sorry to bother you.
I'm kind of stuck here.

41:27.944 --> 41:30.913
- Car trouble?
- Yeah. You mind giving me a jump?

41:31.448 --> 41:32.881
Okay.

41:32.949 --> 41:34.610
Appreciate your time.

41:34.951 --> 41:36.646
Not everybody would have stopped.

41:36.953 --> 41:38.978
- You're real sweet.
- Oh, yeah. Thank you.

41:44.961 --> 41:47.452
I can't believe you fell for that.

41:48.465 --> 41:51.559
Well, my grandfather died
trying to jump-start a car.

41:55.972 --> 41:58.964
I'm sorry.
I was just joking around.

41:58.975 --> 42:02.376
I can't believe you fell for that!

42:02.479 --> 42:04.174
Oh, my God.

42:04.481 --> 42:05.947
That was very good.

42:05.982 --> 42:08.143
- My name's Henry.
- I'm Lucy.

42:08.485 --> 42:10.612
Nice to meet you.
You look like a nice...

42:16.493 --> 42:19.826
Hi. Sorry for the delay.
Should be a few minutes.

42:19.996 --> 42:22.464
- No problem. No worries.
- Where you coming from?

42:22.999 --> 42:24.626
Breakfast?

42:25.001 --> 42:26.434
- Yeah.
- How was it?

42:26.503 --> 42:28.300
I had waffles. They were delicious.

42:28.505 --> 42:30.871
I like making little houses
out of waffles.

42:32.509 --> 42:35.342
- You do?
- That's my thing.

42:37.514 --> 42:38.879
- What's your name?
- Lucy.

42:39.015 --> 42:40.346
Hi, I'm Henry.

42:40.517 --> 42:43.509
Okay, pal. When she stops,
just let her pet you. Look cute.

42:44.020 --> 42:47.183
Go to the middle of the road.
Thank you. Right there. Perfect.

42:53.530 --> 42:56.397
- Oh, shit.
- Here she comes. Smile.

42:59.536 --> 43:01.060
Where is she?

43:04.541 --> 43:06.406
Oh, my God. Oh, no!

43:08.545 --> 43:10.410
Okay. That didn't work.

43:10.547 --> 43:13.414
Shit your pants? So did I.

43:19.055 --> 43:21.023
Okay, this is her.
Start beating me up.

43:21.057 --> 43:22.718
Make it look good.

43:26.062 --> 43:27.689
Give me your wallet!

43:28.064 --> 43:31.158
Okay, haole, what do you think?
You can come to this island...

43:31.568 --> 43:34.469
- ... eat our pineapple...
- Help me! Not so hard.

43:34.571 --> 43:36.704
- Take it easy.
- Try to bang our women.

43:36.739 --> 43:38.837
Making my sister
clean your hotel room.

43:39.075 --> 43:41.373
Okay. What's that have to do
with this? Relax.

43:41.578 --> 43:44.069
- Hey! Hey! Help me, please!
- Stupid haole!

43:45.081 --> 43:48.278
Yeah, that's right. Take that!
And that! And that!

43:48.585 --> 43:50.052
And that! And that!

43:50.086 --> 43:52.350
You got him. You got him.
Enough. Enough.

43:52.589 --> 43:53.886
- Are you okay?
- Yes, yes...

43:54.090 --> 43:55.580
Okay, I'll be back.
Come here!

43:56.092 --> 43:57.719
No, no! I think he's had enough.

43:58.595 --> 44:00.153
I'm sorry.

44:01.097 --> 44:03.327
My eye!

44:04.601 --> 44:06.831
- You got him!
- Not good enough!

44:07.103 --> 44:08.069
Oh, Kamehameha!

44:08.104 --> 44:10.163
He learned his lesson!

44:10.607 --> 44:12.666
- What's your name?
- My name's Henry.

44:13.109 --> 44:14.940
- You did good.
- Hi. Sorry.

44:15.111 --> 44:16.840
I'm in a community-watch program...

44:17.113 --> 44:18.995
Oh, you crazy bitch!

44:19.030 --> 44:20.878
Yeah, keep running!

44:21.117 --> 44:23.517
Okay, okay, he's... He's gone now.

44:30.126 --> 44:31.957
Not her. False alarm.

44:36.132 --> 44:39.226
Don't worry, I called the cops already.
I'm all set.

44:39.261 --> 44:41.729
Yeah? You all set for this, Mr. Smarty?

44:44.641 --> 44:46.575
- Oh, shit.
- Yeah.

44:46.643 --> 44:50.170
When you're finished playing your
kidnap-victim crap on my daughter...

44:50.205 --> 44:51.374
...come by the house.

44:51.648 --> 44:53.741
Okay.

45:01.658 --> 45:03.182
Oh, boy.

45:10.667 --> 45:12.430
There's something I wanna show you.

45:22.679 --> 45:25.773
We figured it out. She only sings
on days she meets you.

45:26.182 --> 45:28.150
You're kidding me. That song?

45:28.184 --> 45:29.617
That's Mom and Dad's song.

45:29.686 --> 45:32.712
When her mom was alive,
Lucy would have me take that tape...

45:33.189 --> 45:35.606
- ... on every fishing trip I went on.
- Oh, yeah?

45:35.641 --> 45:38.024
Yeah, she knew it would make me
miss her mom...

45:38.194 --> 45:39.957
...and want to come home sooner.

45:40.196 --> 45:44.360
I'm seeing a new side to you, sir.
I gotta tell you, it's grossing me out.

45:46.202 --> 45:47.533
Let me ask you something.

45:47.704 --> 45:50.935
What's in it for you?
What do you get out of this?

45:52.709 --> 45:54.040
I don't know.

45:59.215 --> 46:01.740
Wouldn't you want to spend
an hour a day with that?

46:01.775 --> 46:04.551
Actually, no. She sings like shit.

46:05.221 --> 46:07.689
- What?
- Can I ask you guys something?

46:07.724 --> 46:10.557
What'll happen down the line?
Someday she'll wake up...

46:10.727 --> 46:13.924
...look in the mirror and notice
she aged 10 years overnight.

46:14.230 --> 46:16.197
You know something, Henry?

46:16.232 --> 46:19.030
I worry about that
every damn day of my life.

46:24.240 --> 46:25.730
Pardon me.

46:25.742 --> 46:28.836
Sorry to interrupt, but I noticed we
were both eating alone...

46:29.245 --> 46:32.703
...and I thought I could sit with you,
maybe build a syrup Jacuzzi...

46:32.749 --> 46:35.980
- ... for your waffle house?
- Oh, that would be nice...

46:36.252 --> 46:38.550
...but I have a boyfriend.

46:38.755 --> 46:40.780
So I'm sorry.

46:42.759 --> 46:45.125
You're making up a boyfriend
to get rid of me?

46:45.261 --> 46:46.660
No, I'm not.

46:46.763 --> 46:48.856
What's his name, then?

46:48.891 --> 46:50.027
Ringo.

46:50.767 --> 46:52.325
Is his last name Starr?

46:52.769 --> 46:55.761
- No. McCartney.
- McCartney, okay.

46:56.272 --> 46:58.103
- Oh, no.
- All right. I'm sorry.

46:58.274 --> 47:00.674
No! This cop is writing me a ticket!

47:01.277 --> 47:03.268
Oh, whoa, whoa.
I wouldn't go out there.

47:03.279 --> 47:04.678
- Wait, wait, wait!
- Go on!

47:04.781 --> 47:06.146
I'm coming.

47:06.282 --> 47:08.273
The tags don't expire
for seven months.

47:08.284 --> 47:11.082
- They expired May of this year.
- No! No, no!

47:11.287 --> 47:12.754
They expire May of next year.

47:13.289 --> 47:15.280
I think there's been
a misunderstanding.

47:15.291 --> 47:17.020
- I don't.
- This is ridiculous.

47:17.293 --> 47:19.523
I'm not paying for this!
It's October!

47:19.796 --> 47:22.264
Excuse me. Can I borrow this?
Look, October!

47:22.298 --> 47:24.163
Lucy, let's go back inside.

47:25.301 --> 47:27.030
What?

47:36.813 --> 47:38.303
What?

47:44.821 --> 47:46.948
Having a bad day, Doug!

48:28.364 --> 48:30.127
Sweetheart...

48:30.867 --> 48:32.630
...these are from the accident.

48:49.886 --> 48:52.616
Oh, no!

48:59.896 --> 49:02.296
I can feel it.

49:04.400 --> 49:07.927
You were in the hospital
for three months, sweetheart.

49:20.917 --> 49:25.115
I have to talk to this doctor.
I need to hear it from him.

49:25.421 --> 49:27.412
You have heard it, sweetie.
Many times.

49:29.425 --> 49:30.824
I have?

49:32.428 --> 49:33.986
I'll take her.

49:35.431 --> 49:38.093
I have to hear for myself too.

49:48.945 --> 49:51.140
Doug, just take this, okay?
I can't...

49:51.175 --> 49:53.609
I can't look at it anymore.

49:54.450 --> 49:58.079
- It's gonna be all right, Luce.
- Don't call me Luce. I barely know you.

49:58.454 --> 50:00.684
Sweetie, you're sort of dating him.

50:01.958 --> 50:04.324
Sorry I'm not better-looking.

50:06.462 --> 50:09.090
What else happened
since last October?

50:09.465 --> 50:13.265
- What about my students?
- Miss Campbell took over your class.

50:15.972 --> 50:18.907
- Did Alicia marry that guy?
- Yeah.

50:18.975 --> 50:21.341
Doug, did you win
the Mr. Hawaii contest?

50:21.477 --> 50:23.775
I didn't know there was gonna be
a urine test.

50:24.480 --> 50:25.708
Wow.

50:26.983 --> 50:28.348
Do we have sex?

50:29.986 --> 50:33.854
No, we don't.
Just so everybody knows that.

50:34.991 --> 50:36.219
We want to.

50:37.493 --> 50:39.188
Just kidding.

50:42.999 --> 50:46.696
So you guys have to just lie
to me every day.

51:00.516 --> 51:02.643
Hey, Lucy.
Good to see you again.

51:05.521 --> 51:07.614
What the hell's her problem?

51:08.024 --> 51:10.549
She doesn't remember
who you are, brah.

51:10.584 --> 51:12.391
Oh, yeah.

51:12.528 --> 51:15.292
I suck at this job.

51:17.033 --> 51:18.967
Lucy, these are your
brain scans here.

51:19.035 --> 51:21.281
I'm afraid they show
no improvement.

51:21.316 --> 51:23.528
The temporal lobe
was severely damaged.

51:24.040 --> 51:27.008
What we believe is scar tissue
here is impairing your ability...

51:27.043 --> 51:30.706
...to convert short-term memory into
long-term memory while you sleep.

51:31.047 --> 51:33.811
The condition's come to be known
as Goldfield Syndrome.

51:34.050 --> 51:37.247
- Who's Goldfield?
- A brilliant Lithuanian psychiatrist.

51:37.553 --> 51:39.520
He himself suffered
temporal-lobe damage.

51:39.555 --> 51:41.648
Took him four years
to publish his findings...

51:42.058 --> 51:44.720
...because he had to keep
starting over from scratch.

51:45.061 --> 51:48.428
Obviously, your sense of humor
is still intact, and that's here.

51:48.564 --> 51:50.327
Magnificent amygdala as well.

51:50.566 --> 51:53.467
- Doctor, I have a question.
- I'd be happy to answer it...

51:53.569 --> 51:57.972
...but as I've told you before, this is a
hygienic facility. Shirts are required.

51:58.074 --> 51:59.507
- Oh, okay.
- Nice move.

52:01.577 --> 52:03.272
Listen, doctor, this...

52:03.579 --> 52:07.208
...friend of mine's been experimenting
a little with steroids.

52:07.243 --> 52:08.948
He's been having a lot
of wet dreams.

52:09.585 --> 52:11.610
Could there be a connection
between them?

52:11.645 --> 52:13.418
Douglas, get off the juice.

52:13.589 --> 52:16.615
As for the nocturnal emissions,
why don't you take a swim...

52:17.093 --> 52:20.961
...buy a shirt with no holes,
find a wahine and take her to dinner.

52:21.097 --> 52:23.292
I'll tell my friend you said so.

52:24.100 --> 52:26.830
In any case, Lucy,
your condition is stable...

52:27.103 --> 52:28.695
...but most likely permanent.

52:29.105 --> 52:31.039
I'm so sorry, dear.

52:31.107 --> 52:32.802
But it could be worse.

52:34.610 --> 52:35.975
Yeah? How?

52:36.112 --> 52:38.945
I think you should meet
Ten Second Tom.

52:39.031 --> 52:42.762
Callahan Institute is the leading
brain-injury clinic in the Pacific Rim.

52:43.119 --> 52:46.384
We are funded out of Sandusky, Ohio
by T.B. Callahan...

52:46.622 --> 52:49.887
...the automotive-components tycoon
and philanthropist.

52:54.630 --> 52:57.155
And now, I would like
to introduce to you...

52:57.633 --> 53:00.466
...our most distinguished
clinical subject...

53:00.636 --> 53:02.035
...Tom.

53:02.138 --> 53:03.730
- Hi. I'm Tom.
- Henry.

53:03.765 --> 53:04.867
- Marlin.
- Doug.

53:05.141 --> 53:06.369
- Lucy.
- Hi.

53:06.642 --> 53:08.803
Cool flip-flops.
Where'd you get them?

53:09.145 --> 53:12.171
You like those? It's interesting.
I was on the North Shore...

53:12.206 --> 53:13.376
Hi, I'm Tom.

53:14.150 --> 53:16.118
- Henry.
- Hi.

53:16.152 --> 53:18.143
- Marlin.
- Tom lost part of his brain...

53:18.654 --> 53:21.350
...in a hunting accident.
His memory lasts 10 seconds.

53:21.657 --> 53:23.124
I was in an accident? That's terrible.

53:23.159 --> 53:25.286
Don't worry.
You'll get over it in seconds.

53:25.661 --> 53:29.119
Get over it? I mean, what happened?
Did I get shot in the brain...?

53:29.165 --> 53:31.395
- Hi, I'm Tom.
- Hi, I'm Lucy.

53:31.667 --> 53:32.929
- Hi.
- Doug.

53:33.169 --> 53:34.397
- Hey.
- Marlin.

53:34.670 --> 53:37.195
Hey, Tom, can I tell you a secret?

53:39.675 --> 53:42.735
Don't you think you're a little old
to still have wet dreams?

53:46.182 --> 53:49.015
- They liked that.
- Hi, I'm Tom.

53:49.185 --> 53:51.517
- Yeah, watch yourself, Tom.
- Easy.

54:05.701 --> 54:08.101
- I'm gonna go to sleep.
- All right. Good night.

54:08.204 --> 54:10.798
Good night, you guys.
I'll see you tomorrow.

54:12.708 --> 54:15.302
- And I guess I'll see you too?
- Oh, yeah.

54:15.711 --> 54:17.770
You had a rough day today.
I'm sorry.

54:17.805 --> 54:19.908
I hope you get some rest tonight.

54:20.716 --> 54:22.183
Okay.

54:22.218 --> 54:23.685
Good night.

54:24.220 --> 54:25.482
So how you getting home?

54:25.721 --> 54:27.814
- You gonna take the Likelike or...
- Hey.

54:30.226 --> 54:32.956
Thank you for being
so nice to me today.

54:33.229 --> 54:35.789
- Sure.
- I don't want you to...

54:35.824 --> 54:37.426
...strike out tomorrow.

54:37.733 --> 54:39.598
So maybe you could talk
to me about...

54:40.236 --> 54:41.498
...lilies.

54:41.737 --> 54:42.965
Lilies?

54:43.239 --> 54:44.968
I'm a sucker for lilies.

54:45.241 --> 54:46.868
Thanks for the tip.

54:47.243 --> 54:50.075
Good night.

54:50.746 --> 54:52.713
My, oh, my.

54:52.748 --> 54:54.739
- Lover-boy.
- Yes, sir.

54:55.251 --> 54:57.446
You don't have to rush off.
Stick around.

54:57.753 --> 55:00.221
You've earned yourself
a couple beers.

55:01.757 --> 55:03.884
So what'll you do when
you finish the boat?

55:03.919 --> 55:05.624
Actually, I'm going on a trip soon...

55:05.761 --> 55:08.161
...to study undersea
Pacific walrus behaviors.

55:08.264 --> 55:09.595
Sounds kind of fruity.

55:09.765 --> 55:11.995
- Thank you.
- How long is it gonna take?

55:12.268 --> 55:13.496
About a year.

55:13.769 --> 55:15.600
Guess you won't miss days like this.

55:16.272 --> 55:18.968
Well, maybe days like this
don't have to be so bad.

55:19.275 --> 55:21.106
What are you trying to say?

55:22.278 --> 55:23.643
When you guys tell her...

55:23.779 --> 55:26.697
...she's not just finding out
about the accident.

55:26.732 --> 55:29.615
She's finding out that her life
is basically a setup.

55:29.785 --> 55:31.753
I think that freaks her out the most.

55:31.787 --> 55:33.186
- You're an expert now?
- No.

55:33.789 --> 55:36.223
I'm saying I wish there was
another way besides:

55:36.292 --> 55:39.989
"Sorry we couldn't trick you today.
Here's pictures of your broken head. "

55:40.296 --> 55:42.662
- You want a broken head?
- You'll give him one?

55:42.798 --> 55:44.959
No, Daddy, I thought
you was gonna do it.

55:45.301 --> 55:48.065
Nobody's gotta break my head.
I'm gonna split anyways.

55:48.304 --> 55:50.771
Oh, don't go just because
my son is psychotic.

55:50.806 --> 55:54.105
Good night. Sweet dreams.
Keep them dry there, Doug.

55:54.810 --> 55:56.607
Very funny.

56:17.833 --> 56:20.495
- Excuse me. Lucy Whitmore?
- Yes?

56:20.530 --> 56:22.736
I have a delivery for you.

56:23.339 --> 56:25.500
- A delivery for me?
- Yes.

56:27.343 --> 56:30.141
Oh, they're beautiful.

56:30.846 --> 56:33.246
- Who are they from?
- That I can't tell you.

56:33.349 --> 56:36.978
It's a secret admirer.
He also wants you to have this.

56:37.353 --> 56:40.686
- Who's your friend, Lucy?
- Oh, well, I mean, I don't know.

56:40.856 --> 56:43.154
We just met, but look.

56:43.359 --> 56:45.190
I have a secret admirer.

56:45.361 --> 56:47.989
Oh, really? What's this?

56:48.364 --> 56:49.854
It's a videotape.

56:50.366 --> 56:51.833
A videotape of what?

56:51.867 --> 56:54.028
I have no idea.

56:54.370 --> 56:56.167
But I have to find out.

56:57.373 --> 56:58.863
Happy birthday, Daddy.

56:58.874 --> 57:01.900
- Thank you, sweetie.
- That's right. Happy birthday, sir.

57:01.935 --> 57:03.811
- What are you, 200 today?
- That's cute.

57:04.380 --> 57:07.406
- What are you doing?
- I wanted to try something different.

57:07.441 --> 57:09.817
If it doesn't work,
we've only wasted one day.

57:29.405 --> 57:31.168
Martha Stewart faced charges...

57:33.909 --> 57:35.308
Oh, God!

58:15.951 --> 58:17.646
Okay, I think it's on. Go. Go.

58:17.953 --> 58:20.114
Aloha! I'm Henry Roth.

58:20.456 --> 58:26.452
We met here at the Hukilau Cafe
about a year after your accident.

58:26.462 --> 58:29.488
I like you and you like me, most days.

58:29.965 --> 58:33.230
Every day is different, but basically
this is what happens, Lucy.

58:33.469 --> 58:34.902
Kikikoloko, take the camera.

58:34.970 --> 58:36.232
- I got it.
- Don't drop it.

58:36.472 --> 58:38.497
Okay, all right.
Here we are, right here.

58:38.974 --> 58:41.306
The part of you in this reenactment...

58:41.341 --> 58:43.638
...will be played
by my good friend, Ula.

58:44.480 --> 58:47.040
Aloha. Sorry about your brain.

58:47.983 --> 58:49.382
I had a accident too.

58:49.485 --> 58:52.386
Believe it or not, this my good eye.

58:52.988 --> 58:54.216
- We ready?
- Yeah.

58:54.490 --> 58:58.187
Hi. I like that waffle teepee
that you have built.

58:58.494 --> 59:02.396
Oh! So nice of you to notice.
Please, sit down.

59:02.498 --> 59:04.466
I would love to.

59:05.501 --> 59:07.162
My name is Henry, by the way.

59:07.197 --> 59:08.902
My name is Lucy.

59:09.004 --> 59:11.029
Smell my fingers?

59:12.508 --> 59:14.066
Fish. Right on.

59:14.510 --> 59:17.502
So, Lucy, I work at an aquarium.

59:18.013 --> 59:20.481
Aquariums make me super horny.

59:20.516 --> 59:23.178
That's not funny.
Don't rub those.

59:23.519 --> 59:25.510
Sorry, Mr. Whitmore,
if you're watching.

59:25.521 --> 59:27.580
It's very late,
and my friend's unstable.

59:28.023 --> 59:30.719
Come on, stop with the licking!
You're making me sick.

59:30.754 --> 59:32.050
Lucy, I'm sorry.

59:32.528 --> 59:37.056
Anyways, I know you wish I was
making all this stuff up.

59:37.091 --> 59:39.193
I wish I was too.

59:40.536 --> 59:42.002
But the good news is...

59:42.037 --> 59:44.198
...so many people out there
care about you:

59:44.540 --> 59:48.203
Your dad and Doug and a couple
of your friends here at the Hukilau...

59:48.238 --> 59:49.704
...who have a message for you.

59:50.045 --> 59:53.981
Lucy, as you know,
your mother and I were best friends.

59:55.050 --> 59:59.111
That's why I promised her that
I would always help look after you.

01:00:01.056 --> 01:00:04.025
Sometimes life isn't very fair...

01:00:05.060 --> 01:00:06.584
...but we still have you.

01:00:09.064 --> 01:00:12.966
Oh, and if you're wondering about
this guy who's making this tape...

